snippet: Doctors began a partial strike on Monday, abstaining from offering nonemergency services in public hospitals to protest run-down facilities and meager wages, the doctors’ union said.
abstract: Egyptian doctors' union says it has begun partial strike, abstaining from offering nonemergency services in public hospitals to protest run-down facilities and meager wages.
lead_paragraph: Doctors began a partial strike on Monday, abstaining from offering nonemergency services in public hospitals to protest run-down facilities and meager wages, the doctors’ union said.
